Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay coarse, micaceous, mid red-brown. Sampled. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 13 or184, 4 (the latter illustrated here).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1646)
